dct_title_s: Geologic map of the Navajo Country
dct_description_sm: Base compiled by U.S. Geological Survey for map on scale 1:1,000,000 with additional information obtained by Herbert E. Gregory in 1908-1913 ; Geology by Herbert E. Gregory, assisted by K. O. Heald, J. E. Pogue, and W. B. Emery.
Color legend of sedimentary and igneous rocks.
Symbol legend shows "dip and strike," "horizontal bed," "mine or quarry," "Prospect."
Shows railroads, roads, cities and towns, various locations (including ruins) and regions, reservations, waterways, water sources.
From "Geology of the Navajo country, a reconnaissance of parts of Arizona, New Mexico and Utah," published 1917.
